41FrameEncoder::FrameEncoder()
42{
43 m_prevOutputTime = x265_mdate();
44 m_reconfigure = false;
45 m_isFrameEncoder = true;
46 m_threadActive = true;
47 m_slicetypeWaitTime = 0;
48 m_activeWorkerCount = 0;
49 m_completionCount = 0;
50 m_outStreams = NULL;
51 m_backupStreams = NULL;
52 m_substreamSizes = NULL;
53 m_nr = NULL;
54 m_tld = NULL;
55 m_rows = NULL;
56 m_top = NULL;
57 m_param = NULL;
58 m_frame = NULL;
59 m_cuGeoms = NULL;
60 m_ctuGeomMap = NULL;
61 m_localTldIdx = 0;
62 memset(&m_rce, 0, sizeof(RateControlEntry));
63}
64
65void FrameEncoder::destroy()
66{
67 if (m_pool)
68 {
69 if (!m_jpId)
70 {
71 int numTLD = m_pool->m_numWorkers;
72 if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront)
73 numTLD += m_pool->m_numProviders;
74 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
75 m_tld[i].destroy();
76 delete [] m_tld;
77 }
78 }
79 else
80 {
81 m_tld->destroy();
82 delete m_tld;
83 }
84
85 delete[] m_rows;
86 delete[] m_outStreams;
87 delete[] m_backupStreams;
88 X265_FREE(m_sliceBaseRow);
89 X265_FREE((void*)m_bAllRowsStop);
90 X265_FREE((void*)m_vbvResetTriggerRow);
91 X265_FREE(m_sliceMaxBlockRow);
92 X265_FREE(m_cuGeoms);
93 X265_FREE(m_ctuGeomMap);
94 X265_FREE(m_substreamSizes);
95 X265_FREE(m_nr);
96
97 m_frameFilter.destroy();
98
99 if (m_param->bEmitHRDSEI || !!m_param->interlaceMode)
100 {
101 delete m_rce.picTimingSEI;
102 delete m_rce.hrdTiming;
103 }
104}

106bool FrameEncoder::init(Encoder *top, int numRows, int numCols)
107{
108 m_top = top;
109 m_param = top->m_param;
110 m_numRows = numRows;
111 m_numCols = numCols;
112 m_reconfigure = false;
113 m_filterRowDelay = ((m_param->bEnableSAO && m_param->bSaoNonDeblocked)
114 || (!m_param->bEnableLoopFilter && m_param->bEnableSAO)) ?
115 2 : (m_param->bEnableSAO || m_param->bEnableLoopFilter ? 1 : 0);
116 m_filterRowDelayCus = m_filterRowDelay * numCols;
117 m_rows = new CTURow[m_numRows];
118 bool ok = !!m_numRows;
119
120 m_sliceBaseRow = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, m_param->maxSlices + 1);
121 m_bAllRowsStop = X265_MALLOC(bool, m_param->maxSlices);
122 m_vbvResetTriggerRow = X265_MALLOC(int, m_param->maxSlices);
123 ok &= !!m_sliceBaseRow;
124 m_sliceGroupSize = (uint16_t)(m_numRows + m_param->maxSlices - 1) / m_param->maxSlices;
125 uint32_t sliceGroupSizeAccu = (m_numRows << 8) / m_param->maxSlices;
126 uint32_t rowSum = sliceGroupSizeAccu;
127 uint32_t sidx = 0;
128 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numRows; i++)
129 {
130 const uint32_t rowRange = (rowSum >> 8);
131 if ((i >= rowRange) & (sidx != m_param->maxSlices - 1))
132 {
133 rowSum += sliceGroupSizeAccu;
134 m_sliceBaseRow[++sidx] = i;
135 }
136 }
137 X265_CHECK(sidx < m_param->maxSlices, "sliceID check failed!");
138 m_sliceBaseRow[0] = 0;
139 m_sliceBaseRow[m_param->maxSlices] = m_numRows;
140
141 m_sliceMaxBlockRow = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, m_param->maxSlices + 1);
142 ok &= !!m_sliceMaxBlockRow;
143 uint32_t maxBlockRows = (m_param->sourceHeight + (16 - 1)) / 16;
144 sliceGroupSizeAccu = (maxBlockRows << 8) / m_param->maxSlices;
145 rowSum = sliceGroupSizeAccu;
146 sidx = 0;
147 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < maxBlockRows; i++)
148 {
149 const uint32_t rowRange = (rowSum >> 8);
150 if ((i >= rowRange) & (sidx != m_param->maxSlices - 1))
151 {
152 rowSum += sliceGroupSizeAccu;
153 m_sliceMaxBlockRow[++sidx] = i;
154 }
155 }
156 m_sliceMaxBlockRow[0] = 0;
157 m_sliceMaxBlockRow[m_param->maxSlices] = maxBlockRows;
158
159 /* determine full motion search range */
160 int range = m_param->searchRange; /* fpel search */
161 range += !!(m_param->searchMethod < 2); /* diamond/hex range check lag */
162 range += NTAPS_LUMA / 2; /* subpel filter half-length */
163 range += 2 + (MotionEstimate::hpelIterationCount(m_param->subpelRefine) + 1) / 2; /* subpel refine steps */
164 m_refLagRows = /*(m_param->maxSlices > 1 ? 1 : 0) +*/ 1 + ((range + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize);
165
166 // NOTE: 2 times of numRows because both Encoder and Filter in same queue
167 if (!WaveFront::init(m_numRows * 2))
168 {
169 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "unable to initialize wavefront queue\n");
170 m_pool = NULL;
171 }
172
173 m_frameFilter.init(top, this, numRows, numCols);
174
175 // initialize HRD parameters of SPS
176 if (m_param->bEmitHRDSEI || !!m_param->interlaceMode)
177 {
178 m_rce.picTimingSEI = new SEIPictureTiming;
179 m_rce.hrdTiming = new HRDTiming;
180
181 ok &= m_rce.picTimingSEI && m_rce.hrdTiming;
182 }
183
184 if (m_param->noiseReductionIntra || m_param->noiseReductionInter)
185 m_nr = X265_MALLOC(NoiseReduction, 1);
186 if (m_nr)
187 memset(m_nr, 0, sizeof(NoiseReduction));
188 else
189 m_param->noiseReductionIntra = m_param->noiseReductionInter = 0;
190
191 // 7.4.7.1 - Ceil( Log2( PicSizeInCtbsY ) ) bits
192 {
193 unsigned long tmp;
194 CLZ(tmp, (numRows * numCols - 1));
195 m_sliceAddrBits = (uint16_t)(tmp + 1);
196 }
197
198 return ok;
199}
200
201/* Generate a complete list of unique geom sets for the current picture dimensions */
202bool FrameEncoder::initializeGeoms()
203{
204 /* Geoms only vary between CTUs in the presence of picture edges */
205 int maxCUSize = m_param->maxCUSize;
206 int minCUSize = m_param->minCUSize;
207 int heightRem = m_param->sourceHeight & (maxCUSize - 1);
208 int widthRem = m_param->sourceWidth & (maxCUSize - 1);
209 int allocGeoms = 1; // body
210 if (heightRem && widthRem)
211 allocGeoms = 4; // body, right, bottom, corner
212 else if (heightRem || widthRem)
213 allocGeoms = 2; // body, right or bottom
214
215 m_ctuGeomMap = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, m_numRows * m_numCols);
216 m_cuGeoms = X265_MALLOC(CUGeom, allocGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS);
217 if (!m_cuGeoms || !m_ctuGeomMap)
218 return false;
219
220 // body
221 CUData::calcCTUGeoms(maxCUSize, maxCUSize, maxCUSize, minCUSize, m_cuGeoms);
222 memset(m_ctuGeomMap, 0, sizeof(uint32_t) * m_numRows * m_numCols);
223 if (allocGeoms == 1)
224 return true;
225
226 int countGeoms = 1;
227 if (widthRem)
228 {
229 // right
230 CUData::calcCTUGeoms(widthRem, maxCUSize, maxCUSize, minCUSize, m_cuGeoms + countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS);
231 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numRows; i++)
232 {
233 uint32_t ctuAddr = m_numCols * (i + 1) - 1;
234 m_ctuGeomMap[ctuAddr] = countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS;
235 }
236 countGeoms++;
237 }
238 if (heightRem)
239 {
240 // bottom
241 CUData::calcCTUGeoms(maxCUSize, heightRem, maxCUSize, minCUSize, m_cuGeoms + countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS);
242 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numCols; i++)
243 {
244 uint32_t ctuAddr = m_numCols * (m_numRows - 1) + i;
245 m_ctuGeomMap[ctuAddr] = countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS;
246 }
247 countGeoms++;
248
249 if (widthRem)
250 {
251 // corner
252 CUData::calcCTUGeoms(widthRem, heightRem, maxCUSize, minCUSize, m_cuGeoms + countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS);
253
254 uint32_t ctuAddr = m_numCols * m_numRows - 1;
255 m_ctuGeomMap[ctuAddr] = countGeoms * CUGeom::MAX_GEOMS;
256 countGeoms++;
257 }
258 X265_CHECK(countGeoms == allocGeoms, "geometry match check failure\n");
259 }
260
261 return true;
262}
263
264bool FrameEncoder::startCompressFrame(Frame* curFrame)
265{
266 m_slicetypeWaitTime = x265_mdate() - m_prevOutputTime;
267 m_frame = curFrame;
268 m_sliceType = curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType;
269 curFrame->m_encData->m_frameEncoderID = m_jpId;
270 curFrame->m_encData->m_jobProvider = this;
271 curFrame->m_encData->m_slice->m_mref = m_mref;
272
273 if (!m_cuGeoms)
274 {
275 if (!initializeGeoms())
276 return false;
277 }
278
279 m_enable.trigger();
280 return true;
281}
282
283void FrameEncoder::threadMain()
284{
285 THREAD_NAME("Frame", m_jpId);
286
287 if (m_pool)
288 {
289 m_pool->setCurrentThreadAffinity();
290
291 /* the first FE on each NUMA node is responsible for allocating thread
292 * local data for all worker threads in that pool. If WPP is disabled, then
293 * each FE also needs a TLD instance */
294 if (!m_jpId)
295 {
296 int numTLD = m_pool->m_numWorkers;
297 if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront)
298 numTLD += m_pool->m_numProviders;
299
300 m_tld = new ThreadLocalData[numTLD];
301 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
302 {
303 m_tld[i].analysis.initSearch(*m_param, m_top->m_scalingList);
304 m_tld[i].analysis.create(m_tld);
305 }
306
307 for (int i = 0; i < m_pool->m_numProviders; i++)
308 {
309 if (m_pool->m_jpTable[i]->m_isFrameEncoder) /* ugh; over-allocation and other issues here */
310 {
311 FrameEncoder *peer = dynamic_cast<FrameEncoder*>(m_pool->m_jpTable[i]);
312 peer->m_tld = m_tld;
313 }
314 }
315 }
316
317 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
318 m_localTldIdx = -1; // cause exception if used
319 else
320 m_localTldIdx = m_pool->m_numWorkers + m_jpId;
321 }
322 else
323 {
324 m_tld = new ThreadLocalData;
325 m_tld->analysis.initSearch(*m_param, m_top->m_scalingList);
326 m_tld->analysis.create(NULL);
327 m_localTldIdx = 0;
328 }
329
330 m_done.trigger(); /* signal that thread is initialized */
331 m_enable.wait(); /* Encoder::encode() triggers this event */
332
333 while (m_threadActive)
334 {
335 if (m_param->bCTUInfo)
336 {
337 while (!m_frame->m_ctuInfo)
338 m_frame->m_copied.wait();
339 }
340 if ((m_param->bAnalysisType == AVC_INFO) && !m_param->analysisSave && !m_param->analysisLoad && !(IS_X265_TYPE_I(m_frame->m_lowres.sliceType)))
341 {
342 while (((m_frame->m_analysisData.interData == NULL && m_frame->m_analysisData.intraData == NULL) || (uint32_t)m_frame->m_poc != m_frame->m_analysisData.poc))
343 m_frame->m_copyMVType.wait();
344 }
345 compressFrame();
346 m_done.trigger(); /* FrameEncoder::getEncodedPicture() blocks for this event */
347 m_enable.wait();
348 }
349}
350
351void FrameEncoder::WeightAnalysis::processTasks(int /* workerThreadId */)
352{
353 Frame* frame = master.m_frame;
354 weightAnalyse(*frame->m_encData->m_slice, *frame, *master.m_param);
355}

358uint32_t getBsLength( int32_t code )
359{
360 uint32_t ucode = (code <= 0) ? -code << 1 : (code << 1) - 1;
361
362 ++ucode;
363 unsigned long idx;
364 CLZ( idx, ucode );
365 uint32_t length = (uint32_t)idx * 2 + 1;
366
367 return length;
368}

370bool FrameEncoder::writeToneMapInfo(x265_sei_payload *payload)
371{
372 bool payloadChange = false;
373 if (m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload != NULL && payload->payloadSize == m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payloadSize)
374 {
375 if (memcmp(m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload, payload->payload, payload->payloadSize) != 0)
376 payloadChange = true;
377 }
378 else
379 {
380 payloadChange = true;
381 if (m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload != NULL)
382 x265_free(m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload);
383 m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload = (uint8_t*)x265_malloc(sizeof(uint8_t)* payload->payloadSize);
384 }
385
386 if (payloadChange)
387 {
388 m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payloadType = payload->payloadType;
389 m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payloadSize = payload->payloadSize;
390 memcpy(m_top->m_prevTonemapPayload.payload, payload->payload, payload->payloadSize);
391 }
392
393 bool isIDR = m_frame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR;
394 return (payloadChange || isIDR);
395}

397void FrameEncoder::writeTrailingSEIMessages()
398{
399 Slice* slice = m_frame->m_encData->m_slice;
400 int planes = (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400) ? 3 : 1;
401 int32_t payloadSize = 0;
402
403 if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 1)
404 {
405 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_method = SEIDecodedPictureHash::MD5;
406 for (int i = 0; i < planes; i++)
407 MD5Final(&m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[i], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_digest[i]);
408 payloadSize = 1 + 16 * planes;
409 }
410 else if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 2)
411 {
412 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_method = SEIDecodedPictureHash::CRC;
413 for (int i = 0; i < planes; i++)
414 crcFinish(m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[i], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_digest[i]);
415 payloadSize = 1 + 2 * planes;
416 }
417 else if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 3)
418 {
419 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_method = SEIDecodedPictureHash::CHECKSUM;
420 for (int i = 0; i < planes; i++)
421 checksumFinish(m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[i], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_digest[i]);
422 payloadSize = 1 + 4 * planes;
423 }
424
425 m_seiReconPictureDigest.setSize(payloadSize);
426 m_seiReconPictureDigest.writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_SUFFIX_SEI, m_nalList, false);
427}
428
429void FrameEncoder::compressFrame()
430{
431 ProfileScopeEvent(frameThread);
432
433 m_startCompressTime = x265_mdate();
434 m_totalActiveWorkerCount = 0;
435 m_activeWorkerCountSamples = 0;
436 m_totalWorkerElapsedTime = 0;
437 m_totalNoWorkerTime = 0;
438 m_countRowBlocks = 0;
439 m_allRowsAvailableTime = 0;
440 m_stallStartTime = 0;
441
442 m_completionCount = 0;
443 memset((void*)m_bAllRowsStop, 0, sizeof(bool) * m_param->maxSlices);
444 memset((void*)m_vbvResetTriggerRow, -1, sizeof(int) * m_param->maxSlices);
445 m_rowSliceTotalBits[0] = 0;
446 m_rowSliceTotalBits[1] = 0;
447
448 m_SSDY = m_SSDU = m_SSDV = 0;
449 m_ssim = 0;
450 m_ssimCnt = 0;
451 memset(&(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats), 0, sizeof(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats));
452
453 if (!m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && m_param->rc.aqMode != X265_AQ_EDGE && m_param->recursionSkipMode == EDGE_BASED_RSKIP)
454 {
455 int height = m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
456 int width = m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
457 intptr_t stride = m_frame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
458
459 if (!computeEdge(m_frame->m_edgeBitPic, m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0], NULL, stride, height, width, false, 1))
460 {
461 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, " Failed to compute edge !");
462 }
463 }
464
465 /* Emit access unit delimiter unless this is the first frame and the user is
466 * not repeating headers (since AUD is supposed to be the first NAL in the access
467 * unit) */
468 Slice* slice = m_frame->m_encData->m_slice;
469
470 if (m_param->bEnableEndOfSequence && m_frame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR && m_frame->m_poc)
471 {
472 m_bs.resetBits();
473 m_nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_EOS, m_bs);
474 }
475
476 if (m_param->bEnableAccessUnitDelimiters && (m_frame->m_poc || m_param->bRepeatHeaders))
477 {
478 m_bs.resetBits();
479 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_bs);
480 m_entropyCoder.codeAUD(*slice);
481 m_bs.writeByteAlignment();
482 m_nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_ACCESS_UNIT_DELIMITER, m_bs);
483 if (m_param->bSingleSeiNal)
484 m_bs.resetBits();
485 }
486 if (m_frame->m_lowres.bKeyframe && m_param->bRepeatHeaders)
487 {
488 if (m_param->bOptRefListLengthPPS)
489 {
490 ScopedLock refIdxLock(m_top->m_sliceRefIdxLock);
491 m_top->updateRefIdx();
492 }
493 if (m_top->m_param->rc.bStatRead && m_top->m_param->bMultiPassOptRPS)
494 {
495 ScopedLock refIdxLock(m_top->m_rpsInSpsLock);
496 if (!m_top->computeSPSRPSIndex())
497 {
498 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "compute commonly RPS failed!\n");
499 m_top->m_aborted = true;
500 }
501 m_top->getStreamHeaders(m_nalList, m_entropyCoder, m_bs);
502 }
503 else
504 m_top->getStreamHeaders(m_nalList, m_entropyCoder, m_bs);
505 }
506
507 if (m_top->m_param->rc.bStatRead && m_top->m_param->bMultiPassOptRPS)
508 m_frame->m_encData->m_slice->m_rpsIdx = (m_top->m_rateControl->m_rce2Pass + m_frame->m_encodeOrder)->rpsIdx;
509
510 // Weighted Prediction parameters estimation.
511 bool bUseWeightP = slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE && slice->m_pps->bUseWeightPred;
512 bool bUseWeightB = slice->m_sliceType == B_SLICE && slice->m_pps->bUseWeightedBiPred;
513
514 WeightParam* reuseWP = NULL;
515 if (m_param->analysisLoad && (bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB))
516 reuseWP = (WeightParam*)m_frame->m_analysisData.wt;
517
518 if (bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB)
519 {
520#if DETAILED_CU_STATS
521 m_cuStats.countWeightAnalyze++;
522 ScopedElapsedTime time(m_cuStats.weightAnalyzeTime);
523#endif
524 if (m_param->analysisLoad)
525 {
526 for (int list = 0; list < slice->isInterB() + 1; list++)
527 {
528 for (int plane = 0; plane < (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400 ? 3 : 1); plane++)
529 {
530 for (int ref = 1; ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[list]; ref++)
531 SET_WEIGHT(slice->m_weightPredTable[list][ref][plane], false, 1 << reuseWP->log2WeightDenom, reuseWP->log2WeightDenom, 0);
532 slice->m_weightPredTable[list][0][plane] = *(reuseWP++);
533 }
534 }
535 }
536 else
537 {
538 WeightAnalysis wa(*this);
539 if (m_pool && wa.tryBondPeers(*this, 1))
540 /* use an idle worker for weight analysis */
541 wa.waitForExit();
542 else
543 weightAnalyse(*slice, *m_frame, *m_param);
544 }
545 }
546 else
547 slice->disableWeights();
548
549 if (m_param->analysisSave && (bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB))
550 reuseWP = (WeightParam*)m_frame->m_analysisData.wt;
551 // Generate motion references
552 int numPredDir = slice->isInterP() ? 1 : slice->isInterB() ? 2 : 0;
553 for (int l = 0; l < numPredDir; l++)
554 {
555 for (int ref = 0; ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[l]; ref++)
556 {
557 WeightParam *w = NULL;
558 if ((bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB) && slice->m_weightPredTable[l][ref][0].wtPresent)
559 w = slice->m_weightPredTable[l][ref];
560 slice->m_refReconPicList[l][ref] = slice->m_refFrameList[l][ref]->m_reconPic;
561 m_mref[l][ref].init(slice->m_refReconPicList[l][ref], w, *m_param);
562 }
563 if (m_param->analysisSave && (bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB))
564 {
565 for (int i = 0; i < (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400 ? 3 : 1); i++)
566 *(reuseWP++) = slice->m_weightPredTable[l][0][i];
567 }
568
569 }
570
571 int numTLD;
572 if (m_pool)
573 numTLD = m_param->bEnableWavefront ? m_pool->m_numWorkers : m_pool->m_numWorkers + m_pool->m_numProviders;
574 else
575 numTLD = 1;
576
577 /* Get the QP for this frame from rate control. This call may block until
578 * frames ahead of it in encode order have called rateControlEnd() */
579 int qp = m_top->m_rateControl->rateControlStart(m_frame, &m_rce, m_top);
580 m_rce.newQp = qp;
581
582 if (m_nr)
583 {
584 if (qp > QP_MAX_SPEC && m_frame->m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize)
585 {
586 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
587 {
588 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].offset = m_top->m_offsetEmergency[qp - QP_MAX_SPEC - 1];
589 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].residualSum = m_top->m_residualSumEmergency;
590 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].count = m_top->m_countEmergency;
591 }
592 }
593 else
594 {
595 if (m_param->noiseReductionIntra || m_param->noiseReductionInter)
596 {
597 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
598 {
599 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].offset = m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].nrOffsetDenoise;
600 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].residualSum = m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].nrResidualSum;
601 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].count = m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].nrCount;
602 }
603 }
604 else
605 {
606 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
607 m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId].offset = NULL;
608 }
609 }
610 }
611
612 /* Clip slice QP to 0-51 spec range before encoding */
613 slice->m_sliceQp = x265_clip3(-QP_BD_OFFSET, QP_MAX_SPEC, qp);
614 if (m_param->bHDR10Opt)
615 {
616 int qpCb = x265_clip3(-12, 0, (int)floor((m_top->m_cB * ((-.46) * qp + 9.26)) + 0.5 ));
617 int qpCr = x265_clip3(-12, 0, (int)floor((m_top->m_cR * ((-.46) * qp + 9.26)) + 0.5 ));
618 slice->m_chromaQpOffset[0] = slice->m_pps->chromaQpOffset[0] + qpCb < -12 ? (qpCb + (-12 - (slice->m_pps->chromaQpOffset[0] + qpCb))) : qpCb;
619 slice->m_chromaQpOffset[1] = slice->m_pps->chromaQpOffset[1] + qpCr < -12 ? (qpCr + (-12 - (slice->m_pps->chromaQpOffset[1] + qpCr))) : qpCr;
620 }
621
622 if (m_param->bOptQpPPS && m_param->bRepeatHeaders)
623 {
624 ScopedLock qpLock(m_top->m_sliceQpLock);
625 for (int i = 0; i < (QP_MAX_MAX + 1); i++)
626 {
627 int delta = slice->m_sliceQp - (i + 1);
628 int codeLength = getBsLength( delta );
629 m_top->m_iBitsCostSum[i] += codeLength;
630 }
631 m_top->m_iFrameNum++;
632 }
633 m_initSliceContext.resetEntropy(*slice);
634
635 m_frameFilter.start(m_frame, m_initSliceContext);
636
637 /* ensure all rows are blocked prior to initializing row CTU counters */
638 WaveFront::clearEnabledRowMask();
639
640 /* reset entropy coders and compute slice id */
641 m_entropyCoder.load(m_initSliceContext);
642 for (uint32_t sliceId = 0; sliceId < m_param->maxSlices; sliceId++)
643 for (uint32_t row = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]; row < m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1]; row++)
644 m_rows[row].init(m_initSliceContext, sliceId);
645
646 // reset slice counter for rate control update
647 m_sliceCnt = 0;
648
649 uint32_t numSubstreams = m_param->bEnableWavefront ? slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight : m_param->maxSlices;
650 X265_CHECK(m_param->bEnableWavefront || (m_param->maxSlices == 1), "Multiple slices without WPP unsupport now!");
651 if (!m_outStreams)
652 {
653 m_outStreams = new Bitstream[numSubstreams];
654 if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront)
655 m_backupStreams = new Bitstream[numSubstreams];
656 m_substreamSizes = X265_MALLOC(uint32_t, numSubstreams);
657 if (!slice->m_bUseSao)
658 {
659 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numSubstreams; i++)
660 m_rows[i].rowGoOnCoder.setBitstream(&m_outStreams[i]);
661 }
662 }
663 else
664 {
665 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numSubstreams; i++)
666 {
667 m_outStreams[i].resetBits();
668 if (!slice->m_bUseSao)
669 m_rows[i].rowGoOnCoder.setBitstream(&m_outStreams[i]);
670 else
671 m_rows[i].rowGoOnCoder.setBitstream(NULL);
672 }
673 }
674
675 m_rce.encodeOrder = m_frame->m_encodeOrder;
676 int prevBPSEI = m_rce.encodeOrder ? m_top->m_lastBPSEI : 0;
677
678 if (m_frame->m_lowres.bKeyframe)
679 {
680 if (m_param->bEmitHRDSEI)
681 {
682 SEIBufferingPeriod* bpSei = &m_top->m_rateControl->m_bufPeriodSEI;
683
684 // since the temporal layer HRD is not ready, we assumed it is fixed
685 bpSei->m_auCpbRemovalDelayDelta = 1;
686 bpSei->m_cpbDelayOffset = 0;
687 bpSei->m_dpbDelayOffset = 0;
688 bpSei->m_concatenationFlag = (m_param->bEnableHRDConcatFlag && !m_frame->m_poc) ? true : false;
689
690 // hrdFullness() calculates the initial CPB removal delay and offset
691 m_top->m_rateControl->hrdFullness(bpSei);
692 bpSei->writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
693
694 m_top->m_lastBPSEI = m_rce.encodeOrder;
695 }
696
697 if (m_frame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR && m_param->bEmitIDRRecoverySEI)
698 {
699 /* Recovery Point SEI require the SPS to be "activated" */
700 SEIRecoveryPoint sei;
701 sei.m_recoveryPocCnt = 0;
702 sei.m_exactMatchingFlag = true;
703 sei.m_brokenLinkFlag = false;
704 sei.writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
705 }
706 }
707
708 if ((m_param->bEmitHRDSEI || !!m_param->interlaceMode))
709 {
710 SEIPictureTiming *sei = m_rce.picTimingSEI;
711 const VUI *vui = &slice->m_sps->vuiParameters;
712 const HRDInfo *hrd = &vui->hrdParameters;
713 int poc = slice->m_poc;
714
715 if (vui->frameFieldInfoPresentFlag)
716 {
717 if (m_param->interlaceMode > 0)
718 {
719 if( m_param->interlaceMode == 2 )
720 {
721 // m_picStruct should be set to 3 or 4 when field feature is enabled
722 if (m_param->bField)
723 // 3: Top field, bottom field, in that order; 4: Bottom field, top field, in that order
724 sei->m_picStruct = (slice->m_fieldNum == 1) ? 4 : 3;
725 else
726 sei->m_picStruct = (poc & 1) ? 1 /* top */ : 2 /* bottom */;
727 }
728 else if (m_param->interlaceMode == 1)
729 {
730 if (m_param->bField)
731 sei->m_picStruct = (slice->m_fieldNum == 1) ? 3: 4;
732 else
733 sei->m_picStruct = (poc & 1) ? 2 /* bottom */ : 1 /* top */;
734 }
735 }
736 else if (m_param->bEnableFrameDuplication)
737 sei->m_picStruct = m_frame->m_picStruct;
738 else
739 sei->m_picStruct = m_param->pictureStructure;
740
741 sei->m_sourceScanType = m_param->interlaceMode ? 0 : 1;
742
743 sei->m_duplicateFlag = false;
744 }
745
746 if (vui->hrdParametersPresentFlag)
747 {
748 // The m_aucpbremoval delay specifies how many clock ticks the
749 // access unit associated with the picture timing SEI message has to
750 // wait after removal of the access unit with the most recent
751 // buffering period SEI message
752 sei->m_auCpbRemovalDelay = X265_MIN(X265_MAX(1, m_rce.encodeOrder - prevBPSEI), (1 << hrd->cpbRemovalDelayLength));
753 sei->m_picDpbOutputDelay = slice->m_sps->numReorderPics + poc - m_rce.encodeOrder;
754 }
755
756 sei->writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
757 }
758
759 if (m_param->preferredTransferCharacteristics > -1 && slice->isIRAP())
760 {
761 SEIAlternativeTC m_seiAlternativeTC;
762 m_seiAlternativeTC.m_preferredTransferCharacteristics = m_param->preferredTransferCharacteristics;
763 m_seiAlternativeTC.writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
764 }
765
766 /* Write user SEI */
767 for (int i = 0; i < m_frame->m_userSEI.numPayloads; i++)
768 {
769 x265_sei_payload *payload = &m_frame->m_userSEI.payloads[i];
770 if (payload->payloadType == USER_DATA_UNREGISTERED)
771 {
772 SEIuserDataUnregistered sei;
773 sei.m_userData = payload->payload;
774 sei.setSize(payload->payloadSize);
775 sei.writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
776 }
777 else if (payload->payloadType == USER_DATA_REGISTERED_ITU_T_T35)
778 {
779 bool writeSei = m_param->bDhdr10opt ? writeToneMapInfo(payload) : true;
780 if (writeSei)
781 {
782 SEIuserDataRegistered sei;
783 sei.m_userData = payload->payload;
784 sei.setSize(payload->payloadSize);
785 sei.writeSEImessages(m_bs, *slice->m_sps, NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_nalList, m_param->bSingleSeiNal);
786 }
787 }
788 else
789 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Unrecognized SEI type\n");
790 }
791
792 bool isSei = ((m_frame->m_lowres.bKeyframe && m_param->bRepeatHeaders) || m_param->bEmitHRDSEI ||
793 !!m_param->interlaceMode || (m_frame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR && m_param->bEmitIDRRecoverySEI) ||
794 m_frame->m_userSEI.numPayloads);
795
796 if (isSei && m_param->bSingleSeiNal)
797 {
798 m_bs.writeByteAlignment();
799 m_nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI, m_bs);
800 }
801 /* CQP and CRF (without capped VBV) doesn't use mid-frame statistics to
802 * tune RateControl parameters for other frames.
803 * Hence, for these modes, update m_startEndOrder and unlock RC for previous threads waiting in
804 * RateControlEnd here, after the slice contexts are initialized. For the rest - ABR
805 * and VBV, unlock only after rateControlUpdateStats of this frame is called */
806 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode != X265_RC_ABR && !m_top->m_rateControl->m_isVbv)
807 {
808 m_top->m_rateControl->m_startEndOrder.incr();
809
810 if (m_rce.encodeOrder < m_param->frameNumThreads - 1)
811 m_top->m_rateControl->m_startEndOrder.incr(); // faked rateControlEnd calls for negative frames
812 }
813
814 if (m_param->bDynamicRefine)
815 computeAvgTrainingData();
816
817 /* Analyze CTU rows, most of the hard work is done here. Frame is
818 * compressed in a wave-front pattern if WPP is enabled. Row based loop
819 * filters runs behind the CTU compression and reconstruction */
820
821 for (uint32_t sliceId = 0; sliceId < m_param->maxSlices; sliceId++)
822 m_rows[m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]].active = true;
823
824 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
825 {
826 int i = 0;
827 for (uint32_t rowInSlice = 0; rowInSlice < m_sliceGroupSize; rowInSlice++)
828 {
829 for (uint32_t sliceId = 0; sliceId < m_param->maxSlices; sliceId++)
830 {
831 const uint32_t sliceStartRow = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId];
832 const uint32_t sliceEndRow = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1] - 1;
833 const uint32_t row = sliceStartRow + rowInSlice;
834 if (row > sliceEndRow)
835 continue;
836 m_row_to_idx[row] = i;
837 m_idx_to_row[i] = row;
838 i += 1;
839 }
840 }
841 }
842
843 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
844 {
845 for (uint32_t rowInSlice = 0; rowInSlice < m_sliceGroupSize; rowInSlice++)
846 {
847 for (uint32_t sliceId = 0; sliceId < m_param->maxSlices; sliceId++)
848 {
849 const uint32_t sliceStartRow = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId];
850 const uint32_t sliceEndRow = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1] - 1;
851 const uint32_t row = sliceStartRow + rowInSlice;
852
853 X265_CHECK(row < m_numRows, "slices row fault was detected");
854
855 if (row > sliceEndRow)
856 continue;
857
858 // block until all reference frames have reconstructed the rows we need
859 for (int l = 0; l < numPredDir; l++)
860 {
861 for (int ref = 0; ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[l]; ref++)
862 {
863 Frame *refpic = slice->m_refFrameList[l][ref];
864
865 // NOTE: we unnecessary wait row that beyond current slice boundary
866 const int rowIdx = X265_MIN(sliceEndRow, (row + m_refLagRows));
867
868 while (refpic->m_reconRowFlag[rowIdx].get() == 0)
869 refpic->m_reconRowFlag[rowIdx].waitForChange(0);
870
871 if ((bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB) && m_mref[l][ref].isWeighted)
872 m_mref[l][ref].applyWeight(rowIdx, m_numRows, sliceEndRow, sliceId);
873 }
874 }
875
876 enableRowEncoder(m_row_to_idx[row]); /* clear external dependency for this row */
877 if (!rowInSlice)
878 {
879 m_row0WaitTime = x265_mdate();
880 enqueueRowEncoder(m_row_to_idx[row]); /* clear internal dependency, start wavefront */
881 }
882 tryWakeOne();
883 } // end of loop rowInSlice
884 } // end of loop sliceId
885
886 m_allRowsAvailableTime = x265_mdate();
887 tryWakeOne(); /* ensure one thread is active or help-wanted flag is set prior to blocking */
888 static const int block_ms = 250;
889 while (m_completionEvent.timedWait(block_ms))
890 tryWakeOne();
891 }
892 else
893 {
894 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numRows + m_filterRowDelay; i++)
895 {
896 // compress
897 if (i < m_numRows)
898 {
899 // block until all reference frames have reconstructed the rows we need
900 for (int l = 0; l < numPredDir; l++)
901 {
902 int list = l;
903 for (int ref = 0; ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[list]; ref++)
904 {
905 Frame *refpic = slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref];
906
907 const int rowIdx = X265_MIN(m_numRows - 1, (i + m_refLagRows));
908 while (refpic->m_reconRowFlag[rowIdx].get() == 0)
909 refpic->m_reconRowFlag[rowIdx].waitForChange(0);
910
911 if ((bUseWeightP || bUseWeightB) && m_mref[l][ref].isWeighted)
912 m_mref[list][ref].applyWeight(rowIdx, m_numRows, m_numRows, 0);
913 }
914 }
915
916 if (!i)
917 m_row0WaitTime = x265_mdate();
918 else if (i == m_numRows - 1)
919 m_allRowsAvailableTime = x265_mdate();
920 processRowEncoder(i, m_tld[m_localTldIdx]);
921 }
922
923 // filter
924 if (i >= m_filterRowDelay)
925 m_frameFilter.processRow(i - m_filterRowDelay);
926 }
927 }
928#if ENABLE_LIBVMAF
929 vmafFrameLevelScore();
930#endif
931
932 if (m_param->maxSlices > 1)
933 {
934 PicYuv *reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
935 uint32_t height = reconPic->m_picHeight;
936 initDecodedPictureHashSEI(0, 0, height);
937 }
938
939 if (m_param->bDynamicRefine && m_top->m_startPoint <= m_frame->m_encodeOrder) //Avoid collecting data that will not be used by future frames.
940 collectDynDataFrame();
941
942 if (m_param->rc.bStatWrite)
943 {
944 int totalI = 0, totalP = 0, totalSkip = 0;
945
946 // accumulate intra,inter,skip cu count per frame for 2 pass
947 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numRows; i++)
948 {
949 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.mvBits += m_rows[i].rowStats.mvBits;
950 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.coeffBits += m_rows[i].rowStats.coeffBits;
951 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.miscBits += m_rows[i].rowStats.miscBits;
952 totalI += m_rows[i].rowStats.intra8x8Cnt;
953 totalP += m_rows[i].rowStats.inter8x8Cnt;
954 totalSkip += m_rows[i].rowStats.skip8x8Cnt;
955 }
956 int totalCuCount = totalI + totalP + totalSkip;
957 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Intra = (double)totalI / totalCuCount;
958 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Inter = (double)totalP / totalCuCount;
959 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percent8x8Skip = (double)totalSkip / totalCuCount;
960 }
961
962 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 1)
963 {
964 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_numRows; i++)
965 {
966 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntIntraNxN += m_rows[i].rowStats.cntIntraNxN;
967 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu += m_rows[i].rowStats.totalCu;
968 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu += m_rows[i].rowStats.totalCtu;
969 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.lumaDistortion += m_rows[i].rowStats.lumaDistortion;
970 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.chromaDistortion += m_rows[i].rowStats.chromaDistortion;
971 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.psyEnergy += m_rows[i].rowStats.psyEnergy;
972 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.ssimEnergy += m_rows[i].rowStats.ssimEnergy;
973 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.resEnergy += m_rows[i].rowStats.resEnergy;
974 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
975 {
976 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntSkipCu[depth] += m_rows[i].rowStats.cntSkipCu[depth];
977 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntMergeCu[depth] += m_rows[i].rowStats.cntMergeCu[depth];
978 for (int m = 0; m < INTER_MODES; m++)
979 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][m] += m_rows[i].rowStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][m];
980 for (int n = 0; n < INTRA_MODES; n++)
981 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuIntraDistribution[depth][n] += m_rows[i].rowStats.cuIntraDistribution[depth][n];
982 }
983 }
984 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentIntraNxN = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntIntraNxN * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
985
986 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
987 {
988 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentSkipCu[depth] = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntSkipCu[depth] * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
989 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentMergeCu[depth] = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cntMergeCu[depth] * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
990 for (int n = 0; n < INTRA_MODES; n++)
991 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentIntraDistribution[depth][n] = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuIntraDistribution[depth][n] * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
992 uint64_t cuInterRectCnt = 0; // sum of Nx2N, 2NxN counts
993 cuInterRectCnt += m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][1] + m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][2];
994 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentInterDistribution[depth][0] = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][0] * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
995 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentInterDistribution[depth][1] = (double)(cuInterRectCnt * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
996 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.percentInterDistribution[depth][2] = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][3] * 100) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCu;
997 }
998 }
999
1000 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
1001 {
1002 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgLumaDistortion = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.lumaDistortion) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu;
1003 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgChromaDistortion = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.chromaDistortion) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu;
1004 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgPsyEnergy = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.psyEnergy) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu;
1005 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgSsimEnergy = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.ssimEnergy) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu;
1006 m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.avgResEnergy = (double)(m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.resEnergy) / m_frame->m_encData->m_frameStats.totalCtu;
1007 }
1008
1009 m_bs.resetBits();
1010 m_entropyCoder.load(m_initSliceContext);
1011 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_bs);
1012
1013 // finish encode of each CTU row, only required when SAO is enabled
1014 if (slice->m_bUseSao)
1015 encodeSlice(0);
1016
1017 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_bs);
1018
1019 if (m_param->maxSlices > 1)
1020 {
1021 uint32_t nextSliceRow = 0;
1022
1023 for(uint32_t sliceId = 0; sliceId < m_param->maxSlices; sliceId++)
1024 {
1025 m_bs.resetBits();
1026
1027 const uint32_t sliceAddr = nextSliceRow * m_numCols;
1028 if (m_param->bOptRefListLengthPPS)
1029 {
1030 ScopedLock refIdxLock(m_top->m_sliceRefIdxLock);
1031 m_top->analyseRefIdx(slice->m_numRefIdx);
1032 }
1033 m_entropyCoder.codeSliceHeader(*slice, *m_frame->m_encData, sliceAddr, m_sliceAddrBits, slice->m_sliceQp);
1034
1035 // Find rows of current slice
1036 const uint32_t prevSliceRow = nextSliceRow;
1037 while(nextSliceRow < m_numRows && m_rows[nextSliceRow].sliceId == sliceId)
1038 nextSliceRow++;
1039
1040 // serialize each row, record final lengths in slice header
1041 uint32_t maxStreamSize = m_nalList.serializeSubstreams(&m_substreamSizes[prevSliceRow], (nextSliceRow - prevSliceRow), &m_outStreams[prevSliceRow]);
1042
1043 // complete the slice header by writing WPP row-starts
1044 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_bs);
1045 if (slice->m_pps->bEntropyCodingSyncEnabled)
1046 m_entropyCoder.codeSliceHeaderWPPEntryPoints(&m_substreamSizes[prevSliceRow], (nextSliceRow - prevSliceRow - 1), maxStreamSize);
1047
1048 m_bs.writeByteAlignment();
1049
1050 m_nalList.serialize(slice->m_nalUnitType, m_bs);
1051 }
1052 }
1053 else
1054 {
1055 if (m_param->bOptRefListLengthPPS)
1056 {
1057 ScopedLock refIdxLock(m_top->m_sliceRefIdxLock);
1058 m_top->analyseRefIdx(slice->m_numRefIdx);
1059 }
1060 m_entropyCoder.codeSliceHeader(*slice, *m_frame->m_encData, 0, 0, slice->m_sliceQp);
1061
1062 // serialize each row, record final lengths in slice header
1063 uint32_t maxStreamSize = m_nalList.serializeSubstreams(m_substreamSizes, numSubstreams, m_outStreams);
1064
1065 // complete the slice header by writing WPP row-starts
1066 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_bs);
1067 if (slice->m_pps->bEntropyCodingSyncEnabled)
1068 m_entropyCoder.codeSliceHeaderWPPEntryPoints(m_substreamSizes, (slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight - 1), maxStreamSize);
1069 m_bs.writeByteAlignment();
1070
1071 m_nalList.serialize(slice->m_nalUnitType, m_bs);
1072 }
1073
1074 if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI)
1075 writeTrailingSEIMessages();
1076
1077 uint64_t bytes = 0;
1078 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_nalList.m_numNal; i++)
1079 {
1080 int type = m_nalList.m_nal[i].type;
1081
1082 // exclude SEI
1083 if (type != NAL_UNIT_PREFIX_SEI && type != NAL_UNIT_SUFFIX_SEI)
1084 {
1085 bytes += m_nalList.m_nal[i].sizeBytes;
1086 // and exclude start code prefix
1087 bytes -= (!i || type == NAL_UNIT_SPS || type == NAL_UNIT_PPS) ? 4 : 3;
1088 }
1089 }
1090 m_accessUnitBits = bytes << 3;
1091
1092 int filler = 0;
1093 /* rateControlEnd may also block for earlier frames to call rateControlUpdateStats */
1094 if (m_top->m_rateControl->rateControlEnd(m_frame, m_accessUnitBits, &m_rce, &filler) < 0)
1095 m_top->m_aborted = true;
1096
1097 if (filler > 0)
1098 {
1099 filler = (filler - FILLER_OVERHEAD * 8) >> 3;
1100 m_bs.resetBits();
1101 while (filler > 0)
1102 {
1103 m_bs.write(0xff, 8);
1104 filler--;
1105 }
1106 m_bs.writeByteAlignment();
1107 m_nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_FILLER_DATA, m_bs);
1108 bytes += m_nalList.m_nal[m_nalList.m_numNal - 1].sizeBytes;
1109 bytes -= 3; //exclude start code prefix
1110 m_accessUnitBits = bytes << 3;
1111 }
1112
1113 if (m_frame->m_rpu.payloadSize)
1114 {
1115 m_bs.resetBits();
1116 for (int i = 0; i < m_frame->m_rpu.payloadSize; i++)
1117 m_bs.write(m_frame->m_rpu.payload[i], 8);
1118 m_nalList.serialize(NAL_UNIT_UNSPECIFIED, m_bs);
1119 }
1120
1121 m_endCompressTime = x265_mdate();
1122
1123 /* Decrement referenced frame reference counts, allow them to be recycled */
1124 for (int l = 0; l < numPredDir; l++)
1125 {
1126 for (int ref = 0; ref < slice->m_numRefIdx[l]; ref++)
1127 {
1128 Frame *refpic = slice->m_refFrameList[l][ref];
1129 ATOMIC_DEC(&refpic->m_countRefEncoders);
1130 }
1131 }
1132
1133 if (m_nr)
1134 {
1135 bool nrEnabled = (m_rce.newQp < QP_MAX_SPEC || !m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize) && (m_param->noiseReductionIntra || m_param->noiseReductionInter);
1136
1137 if (nrEnabled)
1138 {
1139 /* Accumulate NR statistics from all worker threads */
1140 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
1141 {
1142 NoiseReduction* nr = &m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId];
1143 for (int cat = 0; cat < MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES; cat++)
1144 {
1145 for (int coeff = 0; coeff < MAX_NUM_TR_COEFFS; coeff++)
1146 m_nr->nrResidualSum[cat][coeff] += nr->nrResidualSum[cat][coeff];
1147
1148 m_nr->nrCount[cat] += nr->nrCount[cat];
1149 }
1150 }
1151
1152 noiseReductionUpdate();
1153
1154 /* Copy updated NR coefficients back to all worker threads */
1155 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
1156 {
1157 NoiseReduction* nr = &m_tld[i].analysis.m_quant.m_frameNr[m_jpId];
1158 memcpy(nr->nrOffsetDenoise, m_nr->nrOffsetDenoise, sizeof(uint16_t)* MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES * MAX_NUM_TR_COEFFS);
1159 memset(nr->nrCount, 0, sizeof(uint32_t)* MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES);
1160 memset(nr->nrResidualSum, 0, sizeof(uint32_t)* MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES * MAX_NUM_TR_COEFFS);
1161 }
1162 }
1163 }
1164
1165#if DETAILED_CU_STATS
1166 /* Accumulate CU statistics from each worker thread, we could report
1167 * per-frame stats here, but currently we do not. */
1168 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
1169 m_cuStats.accumulate(m_tld[i].analysis.m_stats[m_jpId], *m_param);
1170#endif
1171
1172 m_endFrameTime = x265_mdate();
1173}
1174
1175void FrameEncoder::initDecodedPictureHashSEI(int row, int cuAddr, int height)
1176{
1177 PicYuv *reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
1178 uint32_t width = reconPic->m_picWidth;
1179 intptr_t stride = reconPic->m_stride;
1180 uint32_t maxCUHeight = m_param->maxCUSize;
1181
1182 const uint32_t hChromaShift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(m_param->internalCsp);
1183 const uint32_t vChromaShift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(m_param->internalCsp);
1184
1185 if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 1)
1186 {
1187 if (!row)
1188 MD5Init(&m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[0]);
1189
1190 updateMD5Plane(m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[0], reconPic->getLumaAddr(cuAddr), width, height, stride);
1191 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1192 {
1193 if (!row)
1194 {
1195 MD5Init(&m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[1]);
1196 MD5Init(&m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[2]);
1197 }
1198
1199 width >>= hChromaShift;
1200 height >>= vChromaShift;
1201 stride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1202
1203 updateMD5Plane(m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[1], reconPic->getCbAddr(cuAddr), width, height, stride);
1204 updateMD5Plane(m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_state[2], reconPic->getCrAddr(cuAddr), width, height, stride);
1205 }
1206 }
1207 else if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 2)
1208 {
1209
1210 if (!row)
1211 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[0] = 0xffff;
1212
1213 updateCRC(reconPic->getLumaAddr(cuAddr), m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[0], height, width, stride);
1214 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1215 {
1216 width >>= hChromaShift;
1217 height >>= vChromaShift;
1218 stride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1219 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[1] = m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[2] = 0xffff;
1220
1221 updateCRC(reconPic->getCbAddr(cuAddr), m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[1], height, width, stride);
1222 updateCRC(reconPic->getCrAddr(cuAddr), m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_crc[2], height, width, stride);
1223 }
1224 }
1225 else if (m_param->decodedPictureHashSEI == 3)
1226 {
1227 if (!row)
1228 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[0] = 0;
1229
1230 updateChecksum(reconPic->m_picOrg[0], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[0], height, width, stride, row, maxCUHeight);
1231 if (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
1232 {
1233 width >>= hChromaShift;
1234 height >>= vChromaShift;
1235 stride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1236 maxCUHeight >>= vChromaShift;
1237
1238 if (!row)
1239 m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[1] = m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[2] = 0;
1240
1241 updateChecksum(reconPic->m_picOrg[1], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[1], height, width, stride, row, maxCUHeight);
1242 updateChecksum(reconPic->m_picOrg[2], m_seiReconPictureDigest.m_checksum[2], height, width, stride, row, maxCUHeight);
1243 }
1244 }
1245}
1246
1247void FrameEncoder::encodeSlice(uint32_t sliceAddr)
1248{
1249 Slice* slice = m_frame->m_encData->m_slice;
1250 const uint32_t widthInLCUs = slice->m_sps->numCuInWidth;
1251 const uint32_t lastCUAddr = (slice->m_endCUAddr + m_param->num4x4Partitions - 1) / m_param->num4x4Partitions;
1252 const uint32_t numSubstreams = m_param->bEnableWavefront ? slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight : 1;
1253
1254 SAOParam* saoParam = slice->m_sps->bUseSAO && slice->m_bUseSao ? m_frame->m_encData->m_saoParam : NULL;
1255 for (uint32_t cuAddr = sliceAddr; cuAddr < lastCUAddr; cuAddr++)
1256 {
1257 uint32_t col = cuAddr % widthInLCUs;
1258 uint32_t row = cuAddr / widthInLCUs;
1259 uint32_t subStrm = row % numSubstreams;
1260 CUData* ctu = m_frame->m_encData->getPicCTU(cuAddr);
1261
1262 m_entropyCoder.setBitstream(&m_outStreams[subStrm]);
1263
1264 // Synchronize cabac probabilities with upper-right CTU if it's available and we're at the start of a line.
1265 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && !col && row)
1266 {
1267 m_entropyCoder.copyState(m_initSliceContext);
1268 m_entropyCoder.loadContexts(m_rows[row - 1].bufferedEntropy);
1269 }
1270
1271 // Initialize slice context
1272 if (ctu->m_bFirstRowInSlice && !col)
1273 m_entropyCoder.load(m_initSliceContext);
1274
1275 if (saoParam)
1276 {
1277 if (saoParam->bSaoFlag[0] || saoParam->bSaoFlag[1])
1278 {
1279 int mergeLeft = col && saoParam->ctuParam[0][cuAddr].mergeMode == SAO_MERGE_LEFT;
1280 int mergeUp = !ctu->m_bFirstRowInSlice && saoParam->ctuParam[0][cuAddr].mergeMode == SAO_MERGE_UP;
1281 if (col)
1282 m_entropyCoder.codeSaoMerge(mergeLeft);
1283 if (!ctu->m_bFirstRowInSlice && !mergeLeft)
1284 m_entropyCoder.codeSaoMerge(mergeUp);
1285 if (!mergeLeft && !mergeUp)
1286 {
1287 if (saoParam->bSaoFlag[0])
1288 m_entropyCoder.codeSaoOffset(saoParam->ctuParam[0][cuAddr], 0);
1289 if (saoParam->bSaoFlag[1])
1290 {
1291 m_entropyCoder.codeSaoOffset(saoParam->ctuParam[1][cuAddr], 1);
1292 m_entropyCoder.codeSaoOffset(saoParam->ctuParam[2][cuAddr], 2);
1293 }
1294 }
1295 }
1296 else
1297 {
1298 for (int i = 0; i < (m_param->internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400 ? 3 : 1); i++)
1299 saoParam->ctuParam[i][cuAddr].reset();
1300 }
1301 }
1302
1303 // final coding (bitstream generation) for this CU
1304 m_entropyCoder.encodeCTU(*ctu, m_cuGeoms[m_ctuGeomMap[cuAddr]]);
1305
1306 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1307 {
1308 if (col == 1)
1309 // Store probabilities of second CTU in line into buffer
1310 m_rows[row].bufferedEntropy.loadContexts(m_entropyCoder);
1311
1312 if (col == widthInLCUs - 1)
1313 m_entropyCoder.finishSlice();
1314 }
1315 }
1316
1317 if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1318 m_entropyCoder.finishSlice();
1319}
1320
1321void FrameEncoder::processRow(int row, int threadId)
1322{
1323 int64_t startTime = x265_mdate();
1324 if (ATOMIC_INC(&m_activeWorkerCount) == 1 && m_stallStartTime)
1325 m_totalNoWorkerTime += x265_mdate() - m_stallStartTime;
1326
1327 const uint32_t realRow = m_idx_to_row[row >> 1];
1328 const uint32_t typeNum = m_idx_to_row[row & 1];
1329
1330 if (!typeNum)
1331 processRowEncoder(realRow, m_tld[threadId]);
1332 else
1333 {
1334 m_frameFilter.processRow(realRow);
1335
1336 // NOTE: Active next row
1337 if (realRow != m_sliceBaseRow[m_rows[realRow].sliceId + 1] - 1)
1338 enqueueRowFilter(m_row_to_idx[realRow + 1]);
1339 }
1340
1341 if (ATOMIC_DEC(&m_activeWorkerCount) == 0)
1342 m_stallStartTime = x265_mdate();
1343
1344 m_totalWorkerElapsedTime += x265_mdate() - startTime; // not thread safe, but good enough
1345}
1346
1347// Called by worker threads
1348void FrameEncoder::processRowEncoder(int intRow, ThreadLocalData& tld)
1349{
1350 const uint32_t row = (uint32_t)intRow;
1351 CTURow& curRow = m_rows[row];
1352
1353 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1354 {
1355 ScopedLock self(curRow.lock);
1356 if (!curRow.active)
1357 /* VBV restart is in progress, exit out */
1358 return;
1359 if (curRow.busy)
1360 {
1361 /* On multi-socket Windows servers, we have seen problems with
1362 * ATOMIC_CAS which resulted in multiple worker threads processing
1363 * the same CU row, which often resulted in bad pointer accesses. We
1364 * believe the problem is fixed, but are leaving this check in place
1365 * to prevent crashes in case it is not */
1366 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING,
1367 "internal error - simultaneous row access detected. Please report HW to x265-devel@videolan.org\n");
1368 return;
1369 }
1370 curRow.busy = true;
1371 }
1372
1373 /* When WPP is enabled, every row has its own row coder instance. Otherwise
1374 * they share row 0 */
1375 Entropy& rowCoder = m_param->bEnableWavefront ? curRow.rowGoOnCoder : m_rows[0].rowGoOnCoder;
1376 FrameData& curEncData = *m_frame->m_encData;
1377 Slice *slice = curEncData.m_slice;
1378
1379 const uint32_t numCols = m_numCols;
1380 const uint32_t lineStartCUAddr = row * numCols;
1381 bool bIsVbv = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0;
1382
1383 const uint32_t sliceId = curRow.sliceId;
1384 uint32_t maxBlockCols = (m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth + (16 - 1)) / 16;
1385 uint32_t noOfBlocks = m_param->maxCUSize / 16;
1386 const uint32_t bFirstRowInSlice = ((row == 0) || (m_rows[row - 1].sliceId != curRow.sliceId)) ? 1 : 0;
1387 const uint32_t bLastRowInSlice = ((row == m_numRows - 1) || (m_rows[row + 1].sliceId != curRow.sliceId)) ? 1 : 0;
1388 const uint32_t endRowInSlicePlus1 = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1];
1389 const uint32_t rowInSlice = row - m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId];
1390
1391 // Load SBAC coder context from previous row and initialize row state.
1392 if (bFirstRowInSlice && !curRow.completed)
1393 rowCoder.load(m_initSliceContext);
1394
1395 // calculate mean QP for consistent deltaQP signalling calculation
1396 if (m_param->bOptCUDeltaQP)
1397 {
1398 ScopedLock self(curRow.lock);
1399 if (!curRow.avgQPComputed)
1400 {
1401 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront || !row)
1402 {
1403 double meanQPOff = 0;
1404 bool isReferenced = IS_REFERENCED(m_frame);
1405 double *qpoffs = (isReferenced && m_param->rc.cuTree) ? m_frame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset : m_frame->m_lowres.qpAqOffset;
1406 if (qpoffs)
1407 {
1408 uint32_t loopIncr = (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8) ? 8 : 16;
1409
1410 uint32_t cuYStart = 0, height = m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
1411 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1412 {
1413 cuYStart = intRow * m_param->maxCUSize;
1414 height = cuYStart + m_param->maxCUSize;
1415 }
1416
1417 uint32_t qgSize = m_param->rc.qgSize, width = m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
1418 uint32_t maxOffsetCols = (m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth + (loopIncr - 1)) / loopIncr;
1419 uint32_t count = 0;
1420 for (uint32_t cuY = cuYStart; cuY < height && (cuY < m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight); cuY += qgSize)
1421 {
1422 for (uint32_t cuX = 0; cuX < width; cuX += qgSize)
1423 {
1424 double qp_offset = 0;
1425 uint32_t cnt = 0;
1426
1427 for (uint32_t block_yy = cuY; block_yy < cuY + qgSize && block_yy < m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight; block_yy += loopIncr)
1428 {
1429 for (uint32_t block_xx = cuX; block_xx < cuX + qgSize && block_xx < width; block_xx += loopIncr)
1430 {
1431 int idx = ((block_yy / loopIncr) * (maxOffsetCols)) + (block_xx / loopIncr);
1432 qp_offset += qpoffs[idx];
1433 cnt++;
1434 }
1435 }
1436 qp_offset /= cnt;
1437 meanQPOff += qp_offset;
1438 count++;
1439 }
1440 }
1441 meanQPOff /= count;
1442 }
1443 rowCoder.m_meanQP = slice->m_sliceQp + meanQPOff;
1444 }
1445 else
1446 {
1447 rowCoder.m_meanQP = m_rows[0].rowGoOnCoder.m_meanQP;
1448 }
1449 curRow.avgQPComputed = 1;
1450 }
1451 }
1452
1453 // Initialize restrict on MV range in slices
1454 tld.analysis.m_sliceMinY = -(int32_t)(rowInSlice * m_param->maxCUSize * 4) + 3 * 4;
1455 tld.analysis.m_sliceMaxY = (int32_t)((endRowInSlicePlus1 - 1 - row) * (m_param->maxCUSize * 4) - 4 * 4);
1456
1457 // Handle single row slice
1458 if (tld.analysis.m_sliceMaxY < tld.analysis.m_sliceMinY)
1459 tld.analysis.m_sliceMaxY = tld.analysis.m_sliceMinY = 0;
1460
1461
1462 while (curRow.completed < numCols)
1463 {
1464 ProfileScopeEvent(encodeCTU);
1465
1466 const uint32_t col = curRow.completed;
1467 const uint32_t cuAddr = lineStartCUAddr + col;
1468 CUData* ctu = curEncData.getPicCTU(cuAddr);
1469 const uint32_t bLastCuInSlice = (bLastRowInSlice & (col == numCols - 1)) ? 1 : 0;
1470 ctu->initCTU(*m_frame, cuAddr, slice->m_sliceQp, bFirstRowInSlice, bLastRowInSlice, bLastCuInSlice);
1471
1472 if (bIsVbv)
1473 {
1474 if (col == 0 && !m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1475 {
1476 m_backupStreams[0].copyBits(&m_outStreams[0]);
1477 curRow.bufferedEntropy.copyState(rowCoder);
1478 curRow.bufferedEntropy.loadContexts(rowCoder);
1479 }
1480 if (bFirstRowInSlice && m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId] != intRow)
1481 {
1482 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQp = curEncData.m_avgQpRc;
1483 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQpScale = x265_qp2qScale(curEncData.m_avgQpRc);
1484 }
1485
1486 FrameData::RCStatCU& cuStat = curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr];
1487 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && rowInSlice >= col && !bFirstRowInSlice && m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId] != intRow)
1488 cuStat.baseQp = curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr - numCols + 1].baseQp;
1489 else if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront && !bFirstRowInSlice && m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId] != intRow)
1490 cuStat.baseQp = curEncData.m_rowStat[row - 1].rowQp;
1491 else
1492 cuStat.baseQp = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQp;
1493
1494 /* TODO: use defines from slicetype.h for lowres block size */
1495 uint32_t block_y = (ctu->m_cuPelY >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize) * noOfBlocks;
1496 uint32_t block_x = (ctu->m_cuPelX >> m_param->maxLog2CUSize) * noOfBlocks;
1497 if (!m_param->analysisLoad || !m_param->bDisableLookahead)
1498 {
1499 cuStat.vbvCost = 0;
1500 cuStat.intraVbvCost = 0;
1501
1502 for (uint32_t h = 0; h < noOfBlocks && block_y < m_sliceMaxBlockRow[sliceId + 1]; h++, block_y++)
1503 {
1504 uint32_t idx = block_x + (block_y * maxBlockCols);
1505
1506 for (uint32_t w = 0; w < noOfBlocks && (block_x + w) < maxBlockCols; w++, idx++)
1507 {
1508 cuStat.vbvCost += m_frame->m_lowres.lowresCostForRc[idx] & LOWRES_COST_MASK;
1509 cuStat.intraVbvCost += m_frame->m_lowres.intraCost[idx];
1510 }
1511 }
1512 }
1513 }
1514 else
1515 curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp = curEncData.m_avgQpRc;
1516
1517 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && !col && !bFirstRowInSlice)
1518 {
1519 // Load SBAC coder context from previous row and initialize row state.
1520 rowCoder.copyState(m_initSliceContext);
1521 rowCoder.loadContexts(m_rows[row - 1].bufferedEntropy);
1522 }
1523 if (m_param->dynamicRd && (int32_t)(m_rce.qpaRc - m_rce.qpNoVbv) > 0)
1524 ctu->m_vbvAffected = true;
1525
1526 // Does all the CU analysis, returns best top level mode decision
1527 Mode& best = tld.analysis.compressCTU(*ctu, *m_frame, m_cuGeoms[m_ctuGeomMap[cuAddr]], rowCoder);
1528
1529 /* startPoint > encodeOrder is true when the start point changes for
1530 a new GOP but few frames from the previous GOP is still incomplete.
1531 The data of frames in this interval will not be used by any future frames. */
1532 if (m_param->bDynamicRefine && m_top->m_startPoint <= m_frame->m_encodeOrder)
1533 collectDynDataRow(*ctu, &curRow.rowStats);
1534
1535 // take a sample of the current active worker count
1536 ATOMIC_ADD(&m_totalActiveWorkerCount, m_activeWorkerCount);
1537 ATOMIC_INC(&m_activeWorkerCountSamples);
1538
1539 /* advance top-level row coder to include the context of this CTU.
1540 * if SAO is disabled, rowCoder writes the final CTU bitstream */
1541 rowCoder.encodeCTU(*ctu, m_cuGeoms[m_ctuGeomMap[cuAddr]]);
1542
1543 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && col == 1)
1544 // Save CABAC state for next row
1545 curRow.bufferedEntropy.loadContexts(rowCoder);
1546
1547 /* SAO parameter estimation using non-deblocked pixels for CTU bottom and right boundary areas */
1548 if (slice->m_bUseSao && m_param->bSaoNonDeblocked)
1549 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row].m_sao.calcSaoStatsCu_BeforeDblk(m_frame, col, row);
1550
1551 /* Deblock with idle threading */
1552 if (m_param->bEnableLoopFilter | slice->m_bUseSao)
1553 {
1554 // NOTE: in VBV mode, we may reencode anytime, so we can't do Deblock stage-Horizon and SAO
1555 if (!bIsVbv)
1556 {
1557 // Delay one row to avoid intra prediction conflict
1558 if (m_pool && !bFirstRowInSlice)
1559 {
1560 int allowCol = col;
1561
1562 // avoid race condition on last column
1563 if (rowInSlice >= 2)
1564 {
1565 allowCol = X265_MIN(((col == numCols - 1) ? m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 2].m_lastDeblocked.get()
1566 : m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 2].m_lastCol.get()), (int)col);
1567 }
1568 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 1].m_allowedCol.set(allowCol);
1569 }
1570
1571 // Last Row may start early
1572 if (m_pool && bLastRowInSlice)
1573 {
1574 // Deblocking last row
1575 int allowCol = col;
1576
1577 // avoid race condition on last column
1578 if (rowInSlice >= 2)
1579 {
1580 allowCol = X265_MIN(((col == numCols - 1) ? m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 1].m_lastDeblocked.get()
1581 : m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 1].m_lastCol.get()), (int)col);
1582 }
1583 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row].m_allowedCol.set(allowCol);
1584 }
1585 } // end of !bIsVbv
1586 }
1587 // Both Loopfilter and SAO Disabled
1588 else
1589 {
1590 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row].processPostCu(col);
1591 }
1592
1593 // Completed CU processing
1594 curRow.completed++;
1595
1596 FrameStats frameLog;
1597 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].sumQpAq += collectCTUStatistics(*ctu, &frameLog);
1598
1599 // copy number of intra, inter cu per row into frame stats for 2 pass
1600 if (m_param->rc.bStatWrite)
1601 {
1602 curRow.rowStats.mvBits += best.mvBits;
1603 curRow.rowStats.coeffBits += best.coeffBits;
1604 curRow.rowStats.miscBits += best.totalBits - (best.mvBits + best.coeffBits);
1605
1606 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
1607 {
1608 /* 1 << shift == number of 8x8 blocks at current depth */
1609 int shift = 2 * (m_param->maxCUDepth - depth);
1610 int cuSize = m_param->maxCUSize >> depth;
1611
1612 curRow.rowStats.intra8x8Cnt += (cuSize == 8) ? (int)(frameLog.cntIntra[depth] + frameLog.cntIntraNxN) :
1613 (int)(frameLog.cntIntra[depth] << shift);
1614
1615 curRow.rowStats.inter8x8Cnt += (int)(frameLog.cntInter[depth] << shift);
1616 curRow.rowStats.skip8x8Cnt += (int)((frameLog.cntSkipCu[depth] + frameLog.cntMergeCu[depth]) << shift);
1617 }
1618 }
1619 curRow.rowStats.totalCtu++;
1620 curRow.rowStats.lumaDistortion += best.lumaDistortion;
1621 curRow.rowStats.chromaDistortion += best.chromaDistortion;
1622 curRow.rowStats.psyEnergy += best.psyEnergy;
1623 curRow.rowStats.ssimEnergy += best.ssimEnergy;
1624 curRow.rowStats.resEnergy += best.resEnergy;
1625 curRow.rowStats.cntIntraNxN += frameLog.cntIntraNxN;
1626 curRow.rowStats.totalCu += frameLog.totalCu;
1627 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth <= m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
1628 {
1629 curRow.rowStats.cntSkipCu[depth] += frameLog.cntSkipCu[depth];
1630 curRow.rowStats.cntMergeCu[depth] += frameLog.cntMergeCu[depth];
1631 for (int m = 0; m < INTER_MODES; m++)
1632 curRow.rowStats.cuInterDistribution[depth][m] += frameLog.cuInterDistribution[depth][m];
1633 for (int n = 0; n < INTRA_MODES; n++)
1634 curRow.rowStats.cuIntraDistribution[depth][n] += frameLog.cuIntraDistribution[depth][n];
1635 }
1636
1637 curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].totalBits = best.totalBits;
1638 x265_emms();
1639
1640 if (bIsVbv)
1641 {
1642 // Update encoded bits, satdCost, baseQP for each CU if tune grain is disabled
1643 FrameData::RCStatCU& cuStat = curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr];
1644 if ((m_param->bEnableWavefront && ((cuAddr == m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId] * numCols) || !m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)) || !m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1645 {
1646 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowSatd += cuStat.vbvCost;
1647 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowIntraSatd += cuStat.intraVbvCost;
1648 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].encodedBits += cuStat.totalBits;
1649 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].sumQpRc += cuStat.baseQp;
1650 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].numEncodedCUs = cuAddr;
1651 }
1652
1653 // If current block is at row end checkpoint, call vbv ratecontrol.
1654 if (!m_param->bEnableWavefront && col == numCols - 1)
1655 {
1656 double qpBase = curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp;
1657 curRow.reEncode = m_top->m_rateControl->rowVbvRateControl(m_frame, row, &m_rce, qpBase, m_sliceBaseRow, sliceId);
1658 qpBase = x265_clip3((double)m_param->rc.qpMin, (double)m_param->rc.qpMax, qpBase);
1659 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQp = qpBase;
1660 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQpScale = x265_qp2qScale(qpBase);
1661 if (curRow.reEncode < 0)
1662 {
1663 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "POC %d row %d - encode restart required for VBV, to %.2f from %.2f\n",
1664 m_frame->m_poc, row, qpBase, curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp);
1665
1666 m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId] = row;
1667 m_outStreams[0].copyBits(&m_backupStreams[0]);
1668
1669 rowCoder.copyState(curRow.bufferedEntropy);
1670 rowCoder.loadContexts(curRow.bufferedEntropy);
1671
1672 curRow.completed = 0;
1673 memset(&curRow.rowStats, 0, sizeof(curRow.rowStats));
1674 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].numEncodedCUs = 0;
1675 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].encodedBits = 0;
1676 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowSatd = 0;
1677 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowIntraSatd = 0;
1678 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].sumQpRc = 0;
1679 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].sumQpAq = 0;
1680 }
1681 }
1682 // If current block is at row diagonal checkpoint, call vbv ratecontrol.
1683 else if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && rowInSlice == col && !bFirstRowInSlice)
1684 {
1685 if (m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)
1686 {
1687 uint32_t startCuAddr = numCols * row;
1688 uint32_t EndCuAddr = startCuAddr + col;
1689
1690 for (int32_t r = row; r >= (int32_t)m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]; r--)
1691 {
1692 for (uint32_t c = startCuAddr; c <= EndCuAddr && c <= numCols * (r + 1) - 1; c++)
1693 {
1694 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowSatd += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].vbvCost;
1695 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowIntraSatd += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].intraVbvCost;
1696 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].encodedBits += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].totalBits;
1697 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].sumQpRc += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].baseQp;
1698 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].numEncodedCUs = c;
1699 }
1700 if (curRow.reEncode < 0)
1701 break;
1702 startCuAddr = EndCuAddr - numCols;
1703 EndCuAddr = startCuAddr + 1;
1704 }
1705 }
1706 double qpBase = curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp;
1707 curRow.reEncode = m_top->m_rateControl->rowVbvRateControl(m_frame, row, &m_rce, qpBase, m_sliceBaseRow, sliceId);
1708 qpBase = x265_clip3((double)m_param->rc.qpMin, (double)m_param->rc.qpMax, qpBase);
1709 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQp = qpBase;
1710 curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQpScale = x265_qp2qScale(qpBase);
1711
1712 if (curRow.reEncode < 0)
1713 {
1714 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "POC %d row %d - encode restart required for VBV, to %.2f from %.2f\n",
1715 m_frame->m_poc, row, qpBase, curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].baseQp);
1716
1717 // prevent the WaveFront::findJob() method from providing new jobs
1718 m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId] = row;
1719 m_bAllRowsStop[curRow.sliceId] = true;
1720
1721 for (uint32_t r = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1] - 1; r >= row; r--)
1722 {
1723 CTURow& stopRow = m_rows[r];
1724
1725 if (r != row)
1726 {
1727 /* if row was active (ready to be run) clear active bit and bitmap bit for this row */
1728 stopRow.lock.acquire();
1729 while (stopRow.active)
1730 {
1731 if (dequeueRow(m_row_to_idx[r] * 2))
1732 stopRow.active = false;
1733 else
1734 {
1735 /* we must release the row lock to allow the thread to exit */
1736 stopRow.lock.release();
1737 GIVE_UP_TIME();
1738 stopRow.lock.acquire();
1739 }
1740 }
1741 stopRow.lock.release();
1742
1743 bool bRowBusy = true;
1744 do
1745 {
1746 stopRow.lock.acquire();
1747 bRowBusy = stopRow.busy;
1748 stopRow.lock.release();
1749
1750 if (bRowBusy)
1751 {
1752 GIVE_UP_TIME();
1753 }
1754 }
1755 while (bRowBusy);
1756 }
1757
1758 m_outStreams[r].resetBits();
1759 stopRow.completed = 0;
1760 memset(&stopRow.rowStats, 0, sizeof(stopRow.rowStats));
1761 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].numEncodedCUs = 0;
1762 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].encodedBits = 0;
1763 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowSatd = 0;
1764 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowIntraSatd = 0;
1765 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].sumQpRc = 0;
1766 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].sumQpAq = 0;
1767 }
1768
1769 m_bAllRowsStop[curRow.sliceId] = false;
1770 }
1771 }
1772 }
1773
1774 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && curRow.completed >= 2 && !bLastRowInSlice &&
1775 (!m_bAllRowsStop[curRow.sliceId] || intRow + 1 < m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId]))
1776 {
1777 /* activate next row */
1778 ScopedLock below(m_rows[row + 1].lock);
1779
1780 if (m_rows[row + 1].active == false &&
1781 m_rows[row + 1].completed + 2 <= curRow.completed)
1782 {
1783 m_rows[row + 1].active = true;
1784 enqueueRowEncoder(m_row_to_idx[row + 1]);
1785 tryWakeOne(); /* wake up a sleeping thread or set the help wanted flag */
1786 }
1787 }
1788
1789 ScopedLock self(curRow.lock);
1790 if ((m_bAllRowsStop[curRow.sliceId] && intRow > m_vbvResetTriggerRow[curRow.sliceId]) ||
1791 (!bFirstRowInSlice && ((curRow.completed < numCols - 1) || (m_rows[row - 1].completed < numCols)) && m_rows[row - 1].completed < curRow.completed + 2))
1792 {
1793 curRow.active = false;
1794 curRow.busy = false;
1795 ATOMIC_INC(&m_countRowBlocks);
1796 return;
1797 }
1798 }
1799
1800 /* this row of CTUs has been compressed */
1801 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront && m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)
1802 {
1803 if (bLastRowInSlice)
1804 {
1805 for (uint32_t r = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]; r < m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1]; r++)
1806 {
1807 for (uint32_t c = curEncData.m_rowStat[r].numEncodedCUs + 1; c < numCols * (r + 1); c++)
1808 {
1809 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowSatd += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].vbvCost;
1810 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].rowIntraSatd += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].intraVbvCost;
1811 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].encodedBits += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].totalBits;
1812 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].sumQpRc += curEncData.m_cuStat[c].baseQp;
1813 curEncData.m_rowStat[r].numEncodedCUs = c;
1814 }
1815 }
1816 }
1817 }
1818
1819 /* If encoding with ABR, update update bits and complexity in rate control
1820 * after a number of rows so the next frame's rateControlStart has more
1821 * accurate data for estimation. At the start of the encode we update stats
1822 * after half the frame is encoded, but after this initial period we update
1823 * after refLagRows (the number of rows reference frames must have completed
1824 * before referencees may begin encoding) */
1825 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_ABR || bIsVbv)
1826 {
1827 uint32_t rowCount = 0;
1828 uint32_t maxRows = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1] - m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId];
1829
1830 if (!m_rce.encodeOrder)
1831 rowCount = maxRows - 1;
1832 else if ((uint32_t)m_rce.encodeOrder <= 2 * (m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom))
1833 rowCount = X265_MIN((maxRows + 1) / 2, maxRows - 1);
1834 else
1835 rowCount = X265_MIN(m_refLagRows / m_param->maxSlices, maxRows - 1);
1836
1837 if (rowInSlice == rowCount)
1838 {
1839 m_rowSliceTotalBits[sliceId] = 0;
1840 if (bIsVbv && !(m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv && m_param->bEnableWavefront))
1841 {
1842 for (uint32_t i = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]; i < rowCount + m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId]; i++)
1843 m_rowSliceTotalBits[sliceId] += curEncData.m_rowStat[i].encodedBits;
1844 }
1845 else
1846 {
1847 uint32_t startAddr = m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId] * numCols;
1848 uint32_t finishAddr = startAddr + rowCount * numCols;
1849
1850 for (uint32_t cuAddr = startAddr; cuAddr < finishAddr; cuAddr++)
1851 m_rowSliceTotalBits[sliceId] += curEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].totalBits;
1852 }
1853
1854 if (ATOMIC_INC(&m_sliceCnt) == (int)m_param->maxSlices)
1855 {
1856 m_rce.rowTotalBits = 0;
1857 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_param->maxSlices; i++)
1858 m_rce.rowTotalBits += m_rowSliceTotalBits[i];
1859 m_top->m_rateControl->rateControlUpdateStats(&m_rce);
1860 }
1861 }
1862 }
1863
1864 /* flush row bitstream (if WPP and no SAO) or flush frame if no WPP and no SAO */
1865 /* end_of_sub_stream_one_bit / end_of_slice_segment_flag */
1866 if (!slice->m_bUseSao && (m_param->bEnableWavefront || bLastRowInSlice))
1867 rowCoder.finishSlice();
1868
1869
1870 /* Processing left Deblock block with current threading */
1871 if ((m_param->bEnableLoopFilter | slice->m_bUseSao) & (rowInSlice >= 2))
1872 {
1873 /* Check conditional to start previous row process with current threading */
1874 if (m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 2].m_lastDeblocked.get() == (int)numCols)
1875 {
1876 /* stop threading on current row and restart it */
1877 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 1].m_allowedCol.set(numCols);
1878 m_frameFilter.m_parallelFilter[row - 1].processTasks(-1);
1879 }
1880 }
1881
1882 /* trigger row-wise loop filters */
1883 if (m_param->bEnableWavefront)
1884 {
1885 if (rowInSlice >= m_filterRowDelay)
1886 {
1887 enableRowFilter(m_row_to_idx[row - m_filterRowDelay]);
1888
1889 /* NOTE: Activate filter if first row (row 0) */
1890 if (rowInSlice == m_filterRowDelay)
1891 enqueueRowFilter(m_row_to_idx[row - m_filterRowDelay]);
1892 tryWakeOne();
1893 }
1894
1895 if (bLastRowInSlice)
1896 {
1897 for (uint32_t i = endRowInSlicePlus1 - m_filterRowDelay; i < endRowInSlicePlus1; i++)
1898 {
1899 enableRowFilter(m_row_to_idx[i]);
1900 }
1901 tryWakeOne();
1902 }
1903
1904 // handle specially case - single row slice
1905 if (bFirstRowInSlice & bLastRowInSlice)
1906 {
1907 enqueueRowFilter(m_row_to_idx[row]);
1908 tryWakeOne();
1909 }
1910 }
1911
1912 curRow.busy = false;
1913
1914 // CHECK_ME: Does it always FALSE condition?
1915 if (ATOMIC_INC(&m_completionCount) == 2 * (int)m_numRows)
1916 m_completionEvent.trigger();
1917}
1918
1919void FrameEncoder::collectDynDataRow(CUData& ctu, FrameStats* rowStats)
1920{
1921 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS; i++)
1922 {
1923 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
1924 {
1925 int offset = (depth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS) + i;
1926 if (ctu.m_collectCUCount[offset])
1927 {
1928 rowStats->rowVarDyn[offset] += ctu.m_collectCUVariance[offset];
1929 rowStats->rowRdDyn[offset] += ctu.m_collectCURd[offset];
1930 rowStats->rowCntDyn[offset] += ctu.m_collectCUCount[offset];
1931 }
1932 }
1933 }
1934}
1935
1936void FrameEncoder::collectDynDataFrame()
1937{
1938 for (uint32_t row = 0; row < m_numRows; row++)
1939 {
1940 for (uint32_t refLevel = 0; refLevel < X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS; refLevel++)
1941 {
1942 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
1943 {
1944 int offset = (depth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS) + refLevel;
1945 int curFrameIndex = m_frame->m_encodeOrder - m_top->m_startPoint;
1946 int index = (curFrameIndex * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS * m_param->maxCUDepth) + offset;
1947 if (m_rows[row].rowStats.rowCntDyn[offset])
1948 {
1949 m_top->m_variance[index] += m_rows[row].rowStats.rowVarDyn[offset];
1950 m_top->m_rdCost[index] += m_rows[row].rowStats.rowRdDyn[offset];
1951 m_top->m_trainingCount[index] += m_rows[row].rowStats.rowCntDyn[offset];
1952 }
1953 }
1954 }
1955 }
1956}
1957
1958void FrameEncoder::computeAvgTrainingData()
1959{
1960 if (m_frame->m_lowres.bScenecut || m_frame->m_lowres.bKeyframe)
1961 {
1962 m_top->m_startPoint = m_frame->m_encodeOrder;
1963 int size = (m_param->keyframeMax + m_param->lookaheadDepth) * m_param->maxCUDepth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS;
1964 memset(m_top->m_variance, 0, size * sizeof(uint64_t));
1965 memset(m_top->m_rdCost, 0, size * sizeof(uint64_t));
1966 memset(m_top->m_trainingCount, 0, size * sizeof(uint32_t));
1967 }
1968 if (m_frame->m_encodeOrder - m_top->m_startPoint < 2 * m_param->frameNumThreads)
1969 m_frame->m_classifyFrame = false;
1970 else
1971 m_frame->m_classifyFrame = true;
1972
1973 int size = m_param->maxCUDepth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS;
1974 memset(m_frame->m_classifyRd, 0, size * sizeof(uint64_t));
1975 memset(m_frame->m_classifyVariance, 0, size * sizeof(uint64_t));
1976 memset(m_frame->m_classifyCount, 0, size * sizeof(uint32_t));
1977 if (m_frame->m_classifyFrame)
1978 {
1979 uint32_t limit = m_frame->m_encodeOrder - m_top->m_startPoint - m_param->frameNumThreads;
1980 for (uint32_t i = 1; i < limit; i++)
1981 {
1982 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS; j++)
1983 {
1984 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
1985 {
1986 int offset = (depth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS) + j;
1987 int index = (i* X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS * m_param->maxCUDepth) + offset;
1988 if (m_top->m_trainingCount[index])
1989 {
1990 m_frame->m_classifyRd[offset] += m_top->m_rdCost[index] / m_top->m_trainingCount[index];
1991 m_frame->m_classifyVariance[offset] += m_top->m_variance[index] / m_top->m_trainingCount[index];
1992 m_frame->m_classifyCount[offset] += m_top->m_trainingCount[index];
1993 }
1994 }
1995 }
1996 }
1997 /* Calculates the average feature values of historic frames that are being considered for the current frame */
1998 int historyCount = m_frame->m_encodeOrder - m_param->frameNumThreads - m_top->m_startPoint - 1;
1999 if (historyCount)
2000 {
2001 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS; j++)
2002 {
2003 for (uint32_t depth = 0; depth < m_param->maxCUDepth; depth++)
2004 {
2005 int offset = (depth * X265_REFINE_INTER_LEVELS) + j;
2006 m_frame->m_classifyRd[offset] /= historyCount;
2007 m_frame->m_classifyVariance[offset] /= historyCount;
2008 }
2009 }
2010 }
2011 }
2012}
2013
2014/* collect statistics about CU coding decisions, return total QP */
2015int FrameEncoder::collectCTUStatistics(const CUData& ctu, FrameStats* log)
2016{
2017 int totQP = 0;
2018 uint32_t depth = 0;
2019 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu.m_numPartitions; absPartIdx += ctu.m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2))
2020 {
2021 depth = ctu.m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
2022 totQP += ctu.m_qp[absPartIdx] * (ctu.m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2));
2023 }
2024
2025 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 1 || m_param->rc.bStatWrite)
2026 {
2027 if (ctu.m_slice->m_sliceType == I_SLICE)
2028 {
2029 depth = 0;
2030 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu.m_numPartitions; absPartIdx += ctu.m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2))
2031 {
2032 depth = ctu.m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
2033
2034 log->totalCu++;
2035 log->cntIntra[depth]++;
2036
2037 if (ctu.m_predMode[absPartIdx] == MODE_NONE)
2038 {
2039 log->totalCu--;
2040 log->cntIntra[depth]--;
2041 }
2042 else if (ctu.m_partSize[absPartIdx] != SIZE_2Nx2N)
2043 {
2044 /* TODO: log intra modes at absPartIdx +0 to +3 */
2045 X265_CHECK(ctu.m_log2CUSize[absPartIdx] == 3 && ctu.m_slice->m_sps->quadtreeTULog2MinSize < 3, "Intra NxN found at improbable depth\n");
2046 log->cntIntraNxN++;
2047 log->cntIntra[depth]--;
2048 }
2049 else if (ctu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx] > 1)
2050 log->cuIntraDistribution[depth][ANGULAR_MODE_ID]++;
2051 else
2052 log->cuIntraDistribution[depth][ctu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx]]++;
2053 }
2054 }
2055 else
2056 {
2057 depth = 0;
2058 for (uint32_t absPartIdx = 0; absPartIdx < ctu.m_numPartitions; absPartIdx += ctu.m_numPartitions >> (depth * 2))
2059 {
2060 depth = ctu.m_cuDepth[absPartIdx];
2061
2062 log->totalCu++;
2063
2064 if (ctu.m_predMode[absPartIdx] == MODE_NONE)
2065 log->totalCu--;
2066 else if (ctu.isSkipped(absPartIdx))
2067 {
2068 if (ctu.m_mergeFlag[0])
2069 log->cntMergeCu[depth]++;
2070 else
2071 log->cntSkipCu[depth]++;
2072 }
2073 else if (ctu.isInter(absPartIdx))
2074 {
2075 log->cntInter[depth]++;
2076
2077 if (ctu.m_partSize[absPartIdx] < AMP_ID)
2078 log->cuInterDistribution[depth][ctu.m_partSize[absPartIdx]]++;
2079 else
2080 log->cuInterDistribution[depth][AMP_ID]++;
2081 }
2082 else if (ctu.isIntra(absPartIdx))
2083 {
2084 log->cntIntra[depth]++;
2085
2086 if (ctu.m_partSize[absPartIdx] != SIZE_2Nx2N)
2087 {
2088 X265_CHECK(ctu.m_log2CUSize[absPartIdx] == 3 && ctu.m_slice->m_sps->quadtreeTULog2MinSize < 3, "Intra NxN found at improbable depth\n");
2089 log->cntIntraNxN++;
2090 log->cntIntra[depth]--;
2091 /* TODO: log intra modes at absPartIdx +0 to +3 */
2092 }
2093 else if (ctu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx] > 1)
2094 log->cuIntraDistribution[depth][ANGULAR_MODE_ID]++;
2095 else
2096 log->cuIntraDistribution[depth][ctu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx]]++;
2097 }
2098 }
2099 }
2100 }
2101
2102 return totQP;
2103}
2104
2105/* DCT-domain noise reduction / adaptive deadzone from libavcodec */
2106void FrameEncoder::noiseReductionUpdate()
2107{
2108 static const uint32_t maxBlocksPerTrSize[4] = {1 << 18, 1 << 16, 1 << 14, 1 << 12};
2109
2110 for (int cat = 0; cat < MAX_NUM_TR_CATEGORIES; cat++)
2111 {
2112 int trSize = cat & 3;
2113 int coefCount = 1 << ((trSize + 2) * 2);
2114
2115 if (m_nr->nrCount[cat] > maxBlocksPerTrSize[trSize])
2116 {
2117 for (int i = 0; i < coefCount; i++)
2118 m_nr->nrResidualSum[cat][i] >>= 1;
2119 m_nr->nrCount[cat] >>= 1;
2120 }
2121
2122 int nrStrength = cat < 8 ? m_param->noiseReductionIntra : m_param->noiseReductionInter;
2123 uint64_t scaledCount = (uint64_t)nrStrength * m_nr->nrCount[cat];
2124
2125 for (int i = 0; i < coefCount; i++)
2126 {
2127 uint64_t value = scaledCount + m_nr->nrResidualSum[cat][i] / 2;
2128 uint64_t denom = m_nr->nrResidualSum[cat][i] + 1;
2129 m_nr->nrOffsetDenoise[cat][i] = (uint16_t)(value / denom);
2130 }
2131
2132 // Don't denoise DC coefficients
2133 m_nr->nrOffsetDenoise[cat][0] = 0;
2134 }
2135}
